<TITLE> PM expresses sorrow at Basu's death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, January 17 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina expressed sorrow at the death of legendary Left leader Jyoti Basu on Sunday. The charismatic Marxist leader, who was born in Sonargaon near Dhaka, died in a Kolkata hospital after battling pneumonia and complications since the new year. He was 95. "I have to give you the sad news that Jyoti babu is no longer with us," Biman Bose, chairperson of the Left Front coordination committee, announced to Indian media a little after 12.30pm local time. His personal physician Dr Ajit Kumar Maity said Basu breathed his last at 11.47am (IST) at the AMRI Hospital, where he was admitted with pneumonia on January 1. He was put on a ventilator on January 6. The veteran leader was in critical condition from late Saturday night after suffering multiple organ failure. Basu was chief minister of West Bengal for 23 years from 1977 at the head of CPI-M-headed Left Front government. He is survived by his son Chandan. His wife Kamal died four years ago
